article.headline: Pacific 64, UC Davis 48
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. -- Ross Rivera scored 19 points and grabbed nine rebounds to lead Pacific to a 64-48 victory over UC Davis Saturday night. Rivera scored 12 points in the second half as Pacific (6-12, 2-4 Big West) increased a lead that reached 20 points three times in the final six minutes. Markus Duran scored 17 points for Pacific, including five 3-pointers. Eddie Miller scored 12 points to lead UC Davis (1-17, 0-6). The Aggies made just 34 percent of their shots from the field and never led. Davis cut a 15-point Pacific lead to 35-25 early in the second half on Tyler Les' 3-pointer, but the Aggies never got any closer as the Tigers answered with a 9-1 run.
